params.side: Side to bid on: Long or Short

params._feePercentage: Fee in tenths of a percent (e.g., 10 = 1%)
params._maturityTime: Unix timestamp of when market resolves
params._strikePrice: Initial strike price (used until market is resolved)

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

bid(uint8).notice: Place a bid during Bidding phase.

claimReward().notice: Users on winning side can claim their reward.

expireMarket().notice: Owner expires the market and enables reward claiming.

getChainlinkDataFeedLatestAnswer().notice: Fetches latest price from Chainlink oracle

getFinalPrice().notice: View function to get final resolved price

resolveMarket().notice: Resolves the market by fetching price from Chainlink oracle.

startBidding().notice: Owner initiates bidding phase from trading phase.

withdraw().notice: Owner withdraws total collected fees from market.
